                <list>
                  <item n="1" xml:id="addition1" syriaca-tags="scribal-colophon doxology">
                    <locus from="254a"/>
                    <p>On fol. 254a, 3rd col., we read the colophon, written with green paint (see also fol. <locus from="227b">227b</locus>):</p>
                    <p><quote xml:lang="syr">$[ܐܫ]ܬܠܡܘ ܒܦܢܩܝܬܐ ܗܕܐ ܟ̈ܬܒܐ ܬ̈ܠܬܐ ܛܛܘܣ ܘܩܠܡܣ ܘܩܣܪܝܐ</quote></p>
                    <p><quote>there are completed in this volume three books, <persName>Titus</persName>, and <persName>Clemens</persName>, and the <persName>Caesarean</persName>.</quote></p>
                    <p>This is followed by the doxologv (written with yellow paint, see also fol. <locus from="229b">229b</locus>), and by the note:</p>
                    <p><quote xml:lang="syr">$ܐܫܬܠܡܬ ܦܢܩܝܕܬܐ$ ܗܕܐ ܒܝܪܚ ܬܫܪܝ ܫܢܬ ܫܒ[ܥܡـ]ܐܐ [ܘܥ]ܣܪܝܢ ܘܬܠܬ ܒ[ܐ]ܘܪܗܝ [ܡܕܝܢܬܐ ܕ]ܒܝܬ [ܢܗ]ܪܝܢ . . .</quote></p>
                    <note>$ܦܢܩܝܬܐ is the oldest form of the word, from <foreign xml:lang="grc">πινακίδὶον</foreign>. It usually becomes, by assimiliation, $ܦܢܩܝܬܐ; and is sometimes corrupted into $ܦܢܩܝܢܬܐ, according to the analogy of $ܡܕܝܢܬܐ  ,ܣܦܝܢܬܐ, etc.</note>
                    <p><quote>this volume was finished in the month of the latter Teshrī, in the year <origDate datingMethod="Seleucid" when-custom="0723">723</origDate> (<origDate calendar="Gregorian" when="0412">A.D. 412</origDate>), at <origPlace><choice><orig>Urhāi</orig><corr resp="http://syriaca.org/editors.xml#wwright">Edessa</corr></choice></origPlace>, a city of <placeName><choice><orig>Beth-Nahrīn</orig><corr resp="http://syriaca.org/editors.xml#wwright">Mesopotamia</corr></choice></placeName>……….</quote></p>                    
                  </item>
                  <item n="2" xml:id="addition2">
